article.headline: Fresno St. 68, UC Davis 57
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- Mike Ladd scored 18 points and Greg Smith added 17 as Fresno State pulled away down the stretch to defeat UC Davis 68-57 on Thursday night. Paul George added 14 points, nine rebounds and six steals for Fresno State (5-5), which shot 56.5 percent from the field. Joe Harden led UC Davis (3-7) with 16 points. Dominic Calegari added 14 points and eight rebounds. After Calegari's layup with 8:09 remaining trimmed Fresno State's lead to 51-49, the Bulldogs put the game away with a 12-2 scoring run. George capped the flurry by stealing the ball at midcourt and dribbling for an open dunk. George then hit a 3-pointer on Fresno State's next possession for a 63-51 lead with 3:52 left. Ladd scored all but one of his points on 3-pointers, finishing 5 of 10 from beyond the arc. Mark Payne added 11 points and eight assists for UCD, which shot 33.3 percent from the field.
